    "title": "Relative Clauses",
    "explanation": "A whole phrase can sit before a noun to describe it. 前にみた嵐 — the storm [that was] seen before. The phrase 前にみた sits directly in front of 嵐.\n\n忘れたもの — the thing [that was] forgotten. 上に飛んだものをみた — saw the thing that flew up.\n\nNo connecting word needed — the modifier simply precedes the noun.\n\nRe-read and find every [verb]た + [noun] pair."
